---
title: Melty Monterey Jack Burgers with Red Onion Jam and Crispy Zucchini
description: There are a lot of burger recipes out there, we know. But we like to think that this is the burger that tops all burgers, thanks to oozy, melty Monterey Jack cheese and jammy balsamic onions. Oh, and we should mention that this patty comes with breaded zucchini on the side, so you can get your fix of crispy, crunchy finger foods and a dose of veg all in one.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5c017fb0e3f3391ceb3d7fc2-3e75241e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/melty-monterey-jack-burgers-5c017fb0e3f3391ceb3d7fc2-32633220.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 890 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/melty-monterey-jack-burgers-5c017fb0e3f3391ceb3d7fc2
---

Adjust oven rack to upper position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{½%teaspoon} until you have ½ tsp (you'll have a clove left over). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Cut @zucchini{2} into 3-inch-long sections, then halve each piece lengthwise. Cut halves into thin wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together @mayonnaise{3%tablespoon} (we sent more) and as much of the garlic as you like (start with a pinch and go up from there). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{2%teaspoon} and @sugar{2%teaspoon}. Continue cooking until syrupy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from pan and set aside in another small bowl. Wash out pan.

While onion cooks, toss together zucchini and 1 TBSP aioli in a #medium bowl{} until wedges are evenly coated. Add @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, @dried oregano{2%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper and toss so that crumbs stick to zucchini. Spread out on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake until panko is golden brown, about ~{15%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

> TIP: It's OK if not all the breadcrumbs stick.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Shape @ground beef{20%ounce} into four patties (make them slightly wider than the buns). Season with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook until patties almost reach desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Sprinkle patties evenly with @Monterey Jack cheese{1%cup}. Cover pan and continue cooking until cheese melts, about ~{1%minute}.

While patties cook, split @potato buns{4} in half and place on another baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden, about ~{3%minutes}. Spread @ketchup{4%tablespoon} and remaining aioli onto buns. Fill each with a beef patty and as much onion jam as you like. Serve with zucchini on the side.